{\fs22\f2 \li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs28\f2 {\b\i\ltrch Customization}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 {\ltrch Keyboard shortcuts}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 \li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 {\ltrch Blender makes heavy use of keyboard shortcuts to speed up work. These can be customized in the Keymap Editor.}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 \li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs30\f2 {\b\i\ltrch Theme colors}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 {\cf3\ltrch Blender allows for most of its interface colors to be changed to suit the needs of the user. If you find that the colors you see on screen do not match those in the Manual, it could be that your default theme has been altered. Creating a new theme or selecting/altering a preexisting one can be done by opening the Preferences and clicking on the Themes tab.}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs30\f2 {\b\i\ltrch Accessibility}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 \li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
{\fs22\f2 {\ltrch Blender has several options for visibility customization, including resolution scale, and the ability to load custom fonts. These settings can be configured in the Interface Preferences.}\li0\ri0\sa0\sb0\fi0\ql\par}
